@endnode
@node "What does it do" "What does it do"

   - It displays a little ANSI with the name of the CD that is online.
   - It shows the User an optional description for the CD (this should
     be 2 lines as max and must have 58 characters as max per line).  
   - It won`t hang the port if a lost carrier occurs.
@endnode
@node "How to install" "How to install"

   Maybe you want that everytime a user enters a direct exchange subboard
   with a CD online the current CD is displayed. Well when just put something
   like that in your sys.entry of this subboard:

   "{#0 PFiles:SRS!_CDiNFo/CDiNFo.rexx CD0:}"
    ^ this is a Ctrl-Q                 ^^^^ here is the devicename

   You will have to give the devicename as an argument (e.g. "CD0:", "CD1:") 

   Preferable you can add the cDiNFO to your PFiles Subboard.
   Then you must adopt it as an arexx script and enter the devicename
   behind the file path/name in the "DOS filename" or in the "Arguments   :"
   line. 

   UnLHa the archive to PFiles: and thats it.. everything should work now.
   Well not really.. you`ll have to have the Commodore Info programm in your
   C: .. but this should be no problem, as it is included with your WB ;)
@endnode
@node "Settings" "Settings"
 
   You can change the text that is print. Look at the beginning of the
   AREXX-script and see what to do.

   And you can change the path where cDiNFO should search for CD descriptions.

   There isn`t more to setup.
@endnode
